TY  - JOUR
T1  - Comment: Decision-Making in Latin American Business
AU  - Prasad, S. Benjamin
Y1  - 1965/12/01
PY  - 1965
DA  - 1965/12/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/255348
DO  - 10.5465/255348
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 324
EP  - 328
VL  - 8
IS  - 4
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - In response to an earlier article in this journal by Eugene Mccann titled ?An Aspect of Management Philosophy in the United States and Latin America,? the article discusses management in Latin America, where the science of management has been slow to take hold. The article provides details of the region in order to develop a framework for introducing management science. Victor Urquidi's book, ?The Challenge of Development in Latin America,? is used as a reference to the typical characteristics of the region, and the issue of science as an attitude or philosophy is discussed. Education, economic development, and attitudes towards scientific and technological research are seen as barriers to the adoption of the study of the science of management.
AB  - In response to an earlier article in this journal by Eugene Mccann titled ?An Aspect of Management Philosophy in the United States and Latin America,? the article discusses management in Latin America, where the science of management has been slow to take hold. The article provides details of the region in order to develop a framework for introducing management science. Victor Urquidi's book, ?The Challenge of Development in Latin America,? is used as a reference to the typical characteristics of the region, and the issue of science as an attitude or philosophy is discussed. Education, economic development, and attitudes towards scientific and technological research are seen as barriers to the adoption of the study of the science of management.
